  "concept": "vuejs/core#12914: parentComponent.ctx.deactivate is not a function while using stable v-for and <keep-alive> ",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:16.551337+00:00",
  "text": "parentComponent.ctx.deactivate is not a function while using stable v-for and <keep-alive> \n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.13\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n[Vue SFC Playground](https://play.vuejs.org/#)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nstep1: click tab2\n\nWhen the v-for directive is used on <keep-alive></keep-alive>, if it is a constant , an error will be reported when switching tabs.\n\n### What is expected?\n\n no error\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n parentComponent.ctx.deactivate is not a function\n\n<img width=\"568\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f942a5dc-5f11-4c6d-801e-b8499d0d20c4\" />\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: keep-alive",
    "has workaround",
    ":hammer: p3-minor-bug"
  ],
